quoridor.model

Class Board

  • java.lang.Object
    • quoridor.model.Board
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Board
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable
    Board class. Stores the 2-dimension array of Squares that represents the game grid, on which the players place their pawn and walls. This class is charged of managing the grid during the course of the game.
    See Also:

      • setNewMove

        public boolean setNewMove(int x,
                          int y,
                          HumanPlayer player)
        Checks if the move at the given coordinates is correct. If it is, this method changes the grid to apply the changes. This method is only used when the player that made the move is a HumanPlayer.
        Parameters:
        x - the x-coordinate of the move
        y - the y-coordinate of the move
        player - the HumanPlayer that made the move
        Returns:
        true if the move is correct and has been applied to the grid, false otherwise

      • setNewMove

        public void setNewMove(int x,
                       int y,
                       AIPlayer player)
        Changes the grid to apply the changes made by the given move. Warning : this method does not check if the given move is correct. It assumes that this checking has been done by the AIPlayer itself. This method is only used when the player that made the move is a AIPlayer.
        Parameters:
        x - the x-coordinate of the move
        y - the y-coordinate of the move
        player - the AIPlayer that made the move
